Key features:
3 bedrooms
2 bathrooms
2 car garage
1477 square feet
Open floor plan 
Spacious kitchen island
Owner's suite boasts a private bathroom and walk-in closet
Covered porch
Close to everything you need and don't need
Quiet, family-friendly neighborhood
HOA neighborhood 
-NO PETS- (Please contact regarding any request for special exception)

This move-in ready, Ashmere style home built in 2021. This stunning home features 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, and a 2 car garage, with a total of 1477 sq ft of living space. The open floor plan and spacious kitchen island are perfect for entertaining and family gatherings. The tranquil owner's suite offers a private bath and walk-in closet, while the covered lanai lets you relax and enjoy the beautiful Florida weather all year round. Home comes with a dishwasher, microwave, electric range with glass top, a refridgerator, and washer/dryer hookups. Bathrooms have upgraded pressurized toilets and all water is treated by the in-garage water softener.
 The neighborhood is small and quiet, with an active HOA community and kids of all ages. 

Close proximity to the community dog park, Sarah Vande Berg Tennis Center, and Silverado Golf Course. Easy access to State Road 301 and 54, Interstate 75, Advent Health, shopping, dining and entertainment in downtown Zephyrhills and YMCA & Zephyr Park recreation options within minutes. The Epperson lagoon (the nation's first Crystal Lagoon), Tampa Outlets, Wiregrass Mall is less than 30 minutes away! PRIME LOCATION
Schedule your private tour today and see for yourself why this is the perfect home for you!

12-month lease
$100 application fee
$2100 security deposit
$2100 monthly rent
$100 late fee
Early termination fee
No pets allowed - Contact for request of exception
No subletting

Owner is furnishing the following: 1 refrigerator , 1 range , 1 dishwasher , 1 air conditioner , 1 water heater , 1 water softener, and window treatments (blinds).

Renter is responsible for maintenance and upkeep of home, appliances, lawn, and abiding by HOA declarations.

Renter is responsible for all utilities on premises as well as any fees resulting from HOA violations.
